The people of Daura, Katsina State, went spiritual on Saturday against the Coronavirus. The Emir of Daura, Alhaji Umar Farouq,led residents in a special prayer session against the deadly infection. The 84-year-old Emir, during the prayer session held at the foreground of his palace, asked residents to see the horrific virus as a test from the Almighty Allah. He urged them to intensify prayers against the outbreak and other untimely death-related diseases. The Emir described the outbreak as deadlier than Boko Haram, and prayed that it would be over as early as possible. He directed all Qur’anic school teachers and clerics of all sects to immediately shut down their centers in strict compliance with the state government’s policy.